class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) return false;
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution works because `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)` will give you the logarithm base 3 of `n`. If `n` is a power of 3, this logarithm will be an integer, and `log % 1 == 0` will be `true`. Otherwise, it will be `false`. The `if (n < 1) return false` part handles the edge cases where `n` is less than 1, as powers of 3 are always positive.

